1
00:00:00,610 --> 00:00:01,610
Really?

2
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:05,980
If we can just land that launch event
for our hotel,

3
00:00:06,310 --> 00:00:08,010
it'll be a huge boost for our group.

4
00:00:08,310 --> 00:00:10,350
A win that big is what we need.

5
00:00:10,350 --> 00:00:12,950
Yes. Our sales have been slow,

6
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:15,420
but I'll be sure to make up for it
with this.

7
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:20,130
Yamamoto is very punctual,
so you'd better be on top of your game.

8
00:00:20,190 --> 00:00:22,490
- Make sure there are no slip-ups.
- I'm well aware.

9
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:26,770
All the necessary documents are ready,
and the meeting is set for tomorrow,

10
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:28,330
so I'll make sure there are no mistakes.

11
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:21,950
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

12
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,760
(Confidential,
Global Brand "P" Launch Event)

13
00:01:28,790 --> 00:01:30,800
(Final Proposal and Future Schedule)

14
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,730
(From: Dream Hotel
Planning and Marketing TF)

15
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:37,800
(To: CEO Yamamoto, P Company)

16
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:47,980
Chae Hwa Young.

17
00:01:48,550 --> 00:01:50,720
I'm going to throw a wrench
in all your plans.

18
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:53,420
Until the pain is so unbearable
that you wish you were dead.

19
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,550
I'm going to crush you
every single chance I get.

20
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:03,500
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

21
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:05,160
The cafe at Samsung Station, right?

22
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,630
We can't be late, so we need to hurry.

23
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,300
We still have plenty of time.

24
00:02:09,670 --> 00:02:11,100
Still, we should get there early.

25
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,910
They said CEO Yamamoto
is extremely punctual.

26
00:02:15,370 --> 00:02:16,570
If we're even a little late,

27
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,940
all of our hard work will have been
for nothing.

28
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:22,010
What?

29
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:29,250
What? Why would CEO Yamamoto use Inline...

30
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:30,660
instead of Telegram?

31
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:33,260
It's probably because he's a foreigner.

32
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:36,260
(Phone issue. Messaging you on Inline)

33
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:37,330
(Can't take calls)

34
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,830
(Could we move
the Samsung Station meeting to 11:00?)

35
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,160
(Flight's delayed, so timing is tight.)

36
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:42,770
What is it?

37
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:45,340
CEO Yamamoto wants to
push back the meeting.

38
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,610
Well, that just gives us
some breathing room.

39
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,610
You said you have an important meeting
today, right?

40
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:58,080
- It'll go great, Mom.
- Thanks.

41
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:05,320
Oh my, hotel coffee.
We've got some time to kill,

42
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:07,160
so it's the perfect time
to sit down for a cup.

43
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:11,230
If the deal goes through,
can I get another car?

44
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:14,100
You already have three cars,
and you want another one?

45
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:16,030
Goodness.

46
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:24,740
I said find my Gapdori right now!

47
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:27,610
Ma'am, please try to calm down.

48
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,950
I don't care if you tear this place apart
or dig through the trash.

49
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:33,150
Just find my Gapdori. Now!

50
00:03:33,450 --> 00:03:35,850
We're sorry. We're checking the CCTV
as fast as we can,

51
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,690
so please, just be patient with us
for a moment.

52
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,120
What's going on here?

53
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:40,760
CEO Chae.

54
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,260
So, you're the one in charge?

55
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:46,530
Is this seriously how you run a hotel?

56
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,000
My darling is missing!

57
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:51,270
Excuse me?

58
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,240
My darling was right here, perfectly fine!
Where did you stash him?

59
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,910
He didn't run off
with some other tramp, did he?

60
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:03,450
No, no, absolutely not. My Gapdori
only has eyes for me. Only me.

61
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:07,250
He's always been completely devoted to me.

62
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:10,250
Gapdori!

63
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,390
My love, Gapdori!

64
00:04:12,490 --> 00:04:14,960
Please come back to me!

65
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:18,460
Ma'am, you can't cause a scene in here.

66
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,330
Why are you looking for your boyfriend
in our hotel?

67
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,340
You should have kept a better eye on him.

68
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:28,240
You can't act like this in public.

69
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,840
What was that?

70
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:36,980
What do you mean I can't manage him?

71
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:40,050
Your hotel is the one that lost him!

72
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:43,350
What is your problem?
You got a death wish?

73
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:46,560
Chae Hwa Young,
soon you're going to wish you were dead.

74
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,830
Goodness!

75
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:58,670
- CEO Chae, are you all right?
- Do I look all right to you?

76
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,240
What time is it?

77
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:03,610
- It's 10:30.
- Are you all right?

78
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,440
You people just don't get it, do you?

79
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:08,280
- Let me help you up.
- Gosh, get off me!

80
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,210
- Are you able to stand?
- Yes.

81
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,580
What should I do?

82
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:13,520
What a relief.

83
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:18,360
- I have time to fix my hair and change.
- Okay, up we go!

84
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:19,760
Are you okay?

85
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:23,160
Hello, is this the police?

86
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:28,530
I was just assaulted by this person,
and I'd like to file a report.

87
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:31,570
What do you think you're doing?

88
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:33,270
You're the one who started it!

89
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,040
I'm so scared.

90
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:36,670
Listen here!

91
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,610
My Gapdori!

92
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:44,420
I left him at the front desk,
but someone left the cage door open,

93
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:47,550
so my Gapdori bolted!

94
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,150
You call this a pet-friendly hotel?

95
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:52,190
Should I complain to the consumer bureau?

96
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:55,830
- We're so sorry.
- It seems someone left his cage open.

97
00:05:56,530 --> 00:05:57,560
Is this him?

98
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,770
Yes, that's him! Gapdori!

99
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:03,230
My baby, where have you been?

100
00:06:04,970 --> 00:06:06,500
I missed you so much.

101
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,340
Get my phone.

102
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,440
Yes, ma'am.

103
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,640
The nerve of some people.

104
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:18,050
I'm going to run to the salon.
I have enough time for that, right?

105
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:21,550
- Yes.
- Seo Rin, bring me a change of clothes.

106
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,020
Okay, Mom.

107
00:06:37,970 --> 00:06:39,870
What an absolute nightmare.

108
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:41,140
What time is it?

109
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:44,580
It's only 10:50.

110
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:50,580
Yes. CEO Yamamoto's secretary.

111
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:54,020
CEO Yamamoto is furious.

112
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,990
What? What are you talking about?

113
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:59,190
You know how particular our CEO is
about being on time.

114
00:06:59,890 --> 00:07:03,430
You're already 50 minutes late
for your 10:00 appointment.

115
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:04,760
What are you talking about?

116
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,730
You're the ones who pushed
the meeting back twice.

117
00:07:08,930 --> 00:07:12,140
- You postponed twice using Inline.
- Inline?

118
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,810
Our CEO may use Telegram...

119
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:17,810
- but he doesn't use Inline at all.
- What did you say?

120
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:21,210
In any case, as far as we're concerned,
the deal is off.

121
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:23,820
Hello? Hello!

122
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:32,920
Who did this?
Who would pull a stunt like this?

123
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,630
CEO Chae, what's going on?

124
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,200
A guilty conscience gives you away.

125
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,970
You did this, didn't you, Jin Hong Ju?

126
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,740
- Are you here to gloat about this mess?
- What?

127
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:51,580
Give it here! Give me your phone!
Let me see your phone!

128
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,910
Why are you doing this?

129
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:59,220
You and your mother did this out of envy.
This was your doing, wasn't it?

130
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,020
You're the one who sabotaged me.

131
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:02,720
If you're innocent, show me your phone!

132
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:05,290
- Let go of me.
- Mom, calm down.

133
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,390
CEO Chae.

134
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:10,660
You and your mother waltz in here
and think you can just push me out.

135
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:13,030
You two are after Dream, aren't you?

136
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:14,400
Say it!

137
00:08:14,570 --> 00:08:18,400
You and your mother seduced the Chairman
like a couple of gold diggers!

138
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,470
Am I wrong?

139
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:24,140
- Let go of me! I said let go!
- Mom, stop! Don't do this!

140
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,950
I'm telling you, I didn't do it.

141
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,820
Stop right there!
You stabbed me in the back, didn't you?

142
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:03,780
Chae Hwa Young,
this is just a taste of what's to come.

143
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:07,150
You're in for a world of pain,
so you'd better look forward to it.

144
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:14,690
What?

145
00:09:15,190 --> 00:09:18,000
The deal fell through
because CEO Chae was late for the meeting?

146
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:19,660
Darn it.

147
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:23,200
And after I told her countless times
to be punctual.

148
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,670
Get CEO Chae in here. Now.

149
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,020
Oh my.

150
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,750
Hong Ju, what happened to you?

151
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,590
- Who did this to you?
- Mom...

152
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:47,160
Oh my goodness.

153
00:09:47,830 --> 00:09:50,330
Gosh, who on earth did this to you?

154
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:53,100
Who dared to lay a hand
on my precious daughter?

155
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:55,470
Was it you?

156
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,500
It was CEO Chae.

157
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,300
CEO Chae grabbed my hair and just...

158
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:06,210
- I'm so humiliated, I could die.
- What? CEO Chae?

159
00:10:06,580 --> 00:10:07,710
What's all this?

160
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:10,880
Honey, can you believe
our daughter-in-law...

161
00:10:11,180 --> 00:10:14,390
manhandled Hong Ju and left her like this?

162
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,550
Father.

163
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:17,220
I've been wrongly accused.

164
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:23,030
- Grandfather.
- Seo Rin, what are you doing?

165
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:25,200
Please, forgive my mother.

166
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:28,300
She was just upset
because the deal fell through.

167
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:30,670
It's not because she hates
Team Leader Jin.

168
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,640
I guess blood really is
thicker than water.

169
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,570
Look at you, taking your mother's side.

170
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:38,180
Come on, get up.
This isn't for you to get involved in.

171
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:42,680
Grandfather,
you'll forgive Mom then, right?

172
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,620
These things happen
in business all the time.

173
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:50,620
Grandfather, I'm begging you.
Please don't be too hard on her, okay?

174
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:53,190
Seo Rin. You have no reason to beg.

175
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,590
Why are you getting involved
when you've done nothing wrong?

176
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:57,330
Mom.

177
00:10:58,800 --> 00:10:59,800
Jin Hong Ju.

178
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:01,770
What lies did you tell them this time?

179
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:06,470
You have some nerve
raising your voice, don’t you?

180
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:09,910
You blew a done deal
because you couldn't even be on time?

181
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:13,810
- You have nothing to say for yourself.
- That's not true.

182
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:18,750
- Jin Hong Ju set me up through Inline.
- That's ridiculous.

183
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:20,550
What would I have to do with Inline?

184
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:23,920
If you're so innocent,
then why won't you let me see your phone?

185
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:25,720
You ran off, didn't you?

186
00:11:26,190 --> 00:11:28,990
I bet you deleted all the evidence
from your phone, didn't you?

187
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:32,800
- I'm being framed!
- I'm the victim here, Father.

188
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,970
If I had landed this contract,

189
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:38,670
it would've completely made up
for last quarter's poor performance.

190
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:39,970
Enough with your excuses.

191
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:43,310
I don't care what happened to you.
This mistake is unacceptable.

192
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:46,680
You've damaged the company,
and you will pay the price.

193
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:51,720
- Father.
- Right. Tell General Affairs...

194
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,680
CEO Chae gets no pay for three months.

195
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,620
Not a pay cut.
No pay at all for three months.

196
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:58,690
Make that clear.

197
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,060
Father, that's too harsh.

198
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:12,240
I'm furious enough
that the Yamamoto deal fell through,

199
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,370
but now that old man has to add
fuel to the fire?

200
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,940
Cutting off my salary?

201
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,340
You might as well just
choke the life out of me!

202
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:21,880
Mom.

203
00:12:22,210 --> 00:12:24,850
- Calm down.
- How am I supposed to calm down?

204
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:28,250
What on earth did I do to have
my entire salary withheld?

205
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,820
It's humiliating. I'm so mad.

206
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:33,290
What's done is done.
There's nothing you can do about it now.

207
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:36,790
You're a capable woman.
If you get a bigger contract next time,

208
00:12:36,930 --> 00:12:39,260
- you can make up for it.
- This was definitely...

209
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,870
the work of Yeom San Wol and her daughter.
It's as clear as day.

210
00:12:50,210 --> 00:12:51,210
It's me.

211
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:55,080
Did you find out who messed with the time
for the Yamamoto meeting?

212
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:58,420
- I'm looking into it now.
- Find out, no matter what it takes.

213
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:02,050
- Mom.
- It must be Yeom San Wol and Jin Hong Ju.

214
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:04,790
As soon as I find proof on those two,

215
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:07,790
I'll kick them out immediately.
I won't let them get away with this.

216
00:13:17,070 --> 00:13:19,770
How dare she when she's beneath me?

217
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,540
My goodness. I raised you so preciously,

218
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:25,880
and I never even laid a finger on you.

219
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,980
And she dared to grab
my beautiful daughter by the hair?

220
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:30,380
- The nerve.
- Mom.

221
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:32,750
I can't just take this anymore.

222
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:37,090
I have to do something,
whether it's revenge or an all-out fight.

223
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,320
That reminds me, Hong Ju.

224
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:42,290
I think someone has some dirt
on Chae Hwa Young.

225
00:13:42,830 --> 00:13:45,600
Something to do with an affair.

226
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,530
Dirt and an affair?

227
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,470
Now that sounds interesting.

228
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:54,510
Nothing gets people talking
like a good affair.

229
00:13:55,470 --> 00:13:56,470
So...

230
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:58,410
who is she having an affair with?

231
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,280
Don't tell me...

232
00:14:00,810 --> 00:14:02,350
you're talking about
Professor Kang Nam Bong?

233
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:06,880
Exactly. Remember I said Chae Hwa Young
and Professor Kang Nam Bong were an item?

234
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:09,350
I took a picture
and tattled to the Chairman,

235
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:13,220
- and that witch made me pay tenfold.
- Mom.

236
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:16,930
Professor Kang Nam Bong
is Lawyer Kang Baek Ho's father.

237
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,460
Didn't I tell you that?

238
00:14:18,930 --> 00:14:22,270
He and his wife are happily married.
How could it be an affair?

239
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:23,870
There's absolutely no way.

240
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:25,400
What do you mean, "no way?"

241
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:29,970
I'd bet my life
Hwa Young was having a fling with him.

242
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:32,040
Denying it won't change a thing.

243
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:35,010
I've got a nose for this sort of thing.

244
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:41,090
- I don't think so.
- Didn't you say you'd fight to the end?

245
00:14:41,890 --> 00:14:43,350
So what do you want to do about it?

246
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:46,490
We need to back her into a corner.

247
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,930
We can't just keep taking this.

248
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:58,040
So that mother and daughter suspect
the affair with Professor Kang.

249
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:01,410
And they're looking for a way
to really screw her over.

250
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:06,540
In that case,
I can't just sit back and do nothing.

251
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,300
"Kang Nam Bong."

252
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:28,730
"Next time, I'll send this to your wife,
Lawyer Han Young Ja."

253
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,370
Who on earth would...

254
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:33,570
Who could it be?

255
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,710
What kind of sick person
sends threats like this?

256
00:15:39,410 --> 00:15:40,410
What?

257
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,380
What was that about blackmail?

258
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:46,080
When did you get home?
It's nothing. Nothing at all.

259
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:48,490
Drinking alone this early?

260
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,720
I was just thirsty.

261
00:15:51,590 --> 00:15:55,090
- You want one? I can get you a can.
- We should eat dinner.

262
00:15:56,190 --> 00:15:57,460
You should stop, too.

263
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:02,670
Look, I know you're a sensitive man.

264
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:05,040
And I'm sure the accident
left you with some trauma.

265
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:08,470
But you're the man of the house.

266
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,540
Seeing you so listless like this...

267
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,940
is a bit disappointing.

268
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:21,290
Why don't you take this opportunity
to see a therapist?

269
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:23,990
A psychiatrist?

270
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,290
Don't act so surprised.

271
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:29,660
These days, for just about anything,

272
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:32,160
people get counseling and treatment.

273
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:34,330
What's the big deal?

274
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,900
Think of it as treating a cold,
but for your mind.

275
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:39,770
They said they'd send it to my wife next.

276
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:43,470
If that happens,
my affair with Hwa Young will be exposed.

277
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:46,910
She'll demand a divorce on the spot.

278
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,850
Just for tonight. Leave me be.

279
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,920
Dream Hotel is partly to blame for this.

280
00:17:05,860 --> 00:17:07,530
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

281
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:08,600
Wait a minute.

282
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:11,140
Director Ma was supposed to
come to the hospital back then.

283
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:14,670
If she's well enough to work,
she can't be that sick.

284
00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:17,810
So why won't CEO Chae
let me see Director Ma?

285
00:17:32,890 --> 00:17:33,890
Seo Rin.

286
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:37,530
Please, hang in there and wake up.

287
00:17:38,730 --> 00:17:39,730
Okay?

288
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:04,720
Baek Ho.

289
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:08,890
What are you doing right now, Baek Ho?

290
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:12,730
You must be so heartbroken
because of me, right?

291
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,330
I'm so sorry.

292
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:27,540
Jang Mi.

293
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:30,050
Please wake up soon.

294
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:33,980
I want to see you smile your bright smile,

295
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:36,920
and snap at me like you used to.

296
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:41,460
I miss that side of you so much.

297
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:55,910
We have vegetables and meat,
and not just meat, but seafood as well.

298
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:58,140
We offer a wide variety for you to enjoy.

299
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:01,880
With so many options, you'll have fun
mixing and matching to your own taste.

300
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:05,580
Oh my, everything looks so fresh.
And there's such a great selection!

301
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:08,290
Right? And we also have
a salad bar over there,

302
00:19:08,390 --> 00:19:11,190
so you can help yourselves
to whatever you'd like.

303
00:19:11,290 --> 00:19:14,660
- Tae Sook, more broth for table six.
- Okay, I'm on it.

304
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:22,870
Tae Sook...

305
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:26,470
I'm so sorry I left you to work so hard
all by yourself.

306
00:19:27,570 --> 00:19:28,940
Please, just wait a little longer.

307
00:19:37,550 --> 00:19:41,620
It seems Baek Ho doesn't know his father
is having an affair with Chae Hwa Young.

308
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:44,690
Gosh, should I tell him or not?

309
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:51,030
Right on cue. Talk about telepathy.

310
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:53,060
How'd he know
I was just thinking about him?

311
00:19:54,630 --> 00:19:55,630
Hey, Baek Ho.

312
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,470
Look, just think about it, Tae Pyung.

313
00:19:57,730 --> 00:20:01,100
I'm sure Director Ma was
in the accident with Jang Mi.

314
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:04,680
But the hit-and-run driver confessed.

315
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,540
If I can just meet with Director Ma,
I'll know for sure.

316
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:10,650
Your brother works at Dream Hotel, right?
Why don't you ask him?

317
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:12,480
I was already planning on asking him.

318
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:17,420
- The Chairman's playing hardball.
- This isn't about my salary.

319
00:20:18,190 --> 00:20:20,690
If I let this slide, I'm finished.

320
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,660
There has to be a way to turn this around.

321
00:20:26,430 --> 00:20:27,430
Oh, wait!

322
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:31,900
You know that annual poll
where women pick the CEO they most admire?

323
00:20:31,970 --> 00:20:35,770
- Yes. The brand image survey.
- That's it.

324
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:41,910
You can quantify ability with numbers,
but image is even more powerful.

325
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:45,650
Even the Chairman can't ignore
public perception.

326
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:48,950
"The CEO Korean women aspire to be like."

327
00:20:48,950 --> 00:20:50,320
With that title alone,

328
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,990
I can more than make up
for the contract I just lost.

329
00:20:55,030 --> 00:20:57,260
- I'll get right on it.
- Hurry.

330
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:00,430
I have to get the upper hand again.

331
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:07,000
Tell Director Ma
I'm still waiting for her answer.

332
00:21:08,470 --> 00:21:10,910
- Pardon?
- She'll know what it means.

333
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:12,840
Understood.

334
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,120
Now that CEO Chae has put me in charge
of Director Ma,

335
00:21:22,650 --> 00:21:24,660
I can't just sit back and do nothing.

336
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,860
Hey, Baek Ho. What's up this late?

337
00:21:32,930 --> 00:21:35,870
Hey, I have to stop by the Dream Hotel.
Can I see you for a minute?

338
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:38,740
Sure. I'll let the front desk know
you're coming, so head on up.

339
00:21:39,270 --> 00:21:40,270
(Shabu Shabu: A Taste of Spring)

340
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,110
(Flavorful Broth,
Various Sauces, Fresh Ingredients)

341
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:43,510
(An Interior That Captures Spring)

342
00:21:43,570 --> 00:21:45,940
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

343
00:21:49,150 --> 00:21:50,180
Director Ma.

344
00:21:50,710 --> 00:21:55,020
General Manager Kang asked me to tell you
that he's still waiting for your answer.

345
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:01,830
I asked if you can analyze the ROI
on our initial investment.

346
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:07,430
Return on investment?
How would I know anything about that?

347
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:11,230
What's the matter?
If it's about work, I can help.

348
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:13,940
You would?

349
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:18,210
I've always done all the work anyway.
Why the surprise?

350
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,440
Such a show-off.

351
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:23,010
Forget it. I'll handle my own work,
so stay out of it.

352
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:35,590
My question must have given you
a lot to think about.

353
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:37,590
Seeing as you're only showing up now.

354
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,330
Have a seat.
You look like you have a lot on your mind.

355
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:49,540
You asked about
the return on investment, correct?

356
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:52,440
I did. Let's hear it.

357
00:22:53,410 --> 00:22:55,250
I've never been very good with numbers.

358
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:02,850
Whether it's a hotel or a resort,
it comes down to food and lodging.

359
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:06,560
But with this layout, the traffic flow
for the restaurant or cafe...

360
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:10,530
isn't designed to make people linger.
Forget about occupancy rates and all that.

361
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:13,660
Profit comes from
how well you win over your guests.

362
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:15,570
And your point is?

363
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,300
This is something I know well
from hands-on experience.

364
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:22,940
When the layout makes people linger,
they eat more and order more coffee.

365
00:23:23,170 --> 00:23:25,110
That's your real profit margin.

366
00:23:33,950 --> 00:23:35,890
Am I interrupting?

367
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:38,020
Not at all. Please, have a seat.

368
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:44,800
What were you talking about
that has you two in such a good mood?

369
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:48,060
Director Ma just made an excellent point.

370
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,070
Our Seo Rin did?

371
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:56,140
Excuse me, I'm here
to see General Manager Kang Jun Ho.

372
00:23:56,310 --> 00:24:00,110
Yes. We've been expecting you.
You're Lawyer Kang Baek Ho, correct?

373
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:02,550
- Yes.
- Please proceed to the ninth floor.

374
00:24:02,810 --> 00:24:04,310
Okay. Thank you.

375
00:24:05,580 --> 00:24:09,490
So, the layout should encourage guests
to stay longer?

376
00:24:09,990 --> 00:24:13,520
I've always considered guest flow
to be a top priority as well.

377
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:16,930
Because I joined the Dream Project late,

378
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:18,730
it took me a while
to get fully up to speed, but...

379
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:21,260
Director Ma pointed it out perfectly.

380
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:23,470
So all that time you spent hanging around
Chang Restaurant...

381
00:24:23,470 --> 00:24:25,340
to see General Manager Kang...

382
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:28,070
finally taught you
the importance of customer flow.

383
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:30,740
I guess you could say that.

384
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:33,610
I'll make the necessary revisions
and issue a new notice.

385
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:36,310
General Manager Kang, you need to guide
the design team on this.

386
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:39,820
After all, you're the one
with the hands-on experience,

387
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,020
so you can give them the proper guidance.

388
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:45,490
- Can I be excused now?
- Go ahead.

389
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:56,070
Have you thought about what I said,
General Manager Kang?

390
00:24:59,940 --> 00:25:01,640
About you marrying my Seo Rin.

391
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:28,300
The doors are closing.

392
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:07,840
(The First Man)

393
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:10,610
- Who did you say is here?
- Professor Kang Nam Bong's wife.

394
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:14,410
My name is Han Young Ja.
I'll get straight to the point.

395
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:17,110
That Chairman Ma and I have hand-picked...

396
00:26:17,110 --> 00:26:19,250
General Manager Kang Jun Ho
for my Seo Rin.

397
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:21,120
Leak the tip through the hotline.

398
00:26:21,450 --> 00:26:23,620
If I start by looking for
the evidence Seo Rin hid,

399
00:26:23,950 --> 00:26:25,860
it'll take way too long.

400
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:29,230
For now, I'll use this video
to tell Grandfather everything.

401
00:26:30,790 --> 00:26:32,800
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
